From: Miaoqian Lin <linmq006@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 11 May 2022 16:07:37 +0400
Subject: [PATCH] rpmsg: qcom_smd: Fix refcount leak in qcom_smd_parse_edge
Git-commit: 65382585f067d4256ba087934f30f85c9b6984de
Patch-mainline: v6.0-rc1
References: git-fixes CVE-2022-50112 bsc#1244832

of_parse_phandle() returns a node pointer with refcount
incremented, we should use of_node_put() on it when done.

Fixes: 53e2822e56c7 ("rpmsg: Introduce Qualcomm SMD backend")
Signed-off-by: Miaoqian Lin <linmq006@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Bjorn Andersson <bjorn.andersson@linaro.org>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20220511120737.57374-1-linmq006@gmail.com
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/rpmsg/qcom_smd.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/rpmsg/qcom_smd.c b/drivers/rpmsg/qcom_smd.c
index c87413a5bf6c..1044cf03c542 100644
--- a/drivers/rpmsg/qcom_smd.c
+++ b/drivers/rpmsg/qcom_smd.c
@@ -1383,6 +1383,7 @@ static int qcom_smd_parse_edge(struct device *dev,
 		}
 
 		edge->ipc_regmap = syscon_node_to_regmap(syscon_np);
+		of_node_put(syscon_np);
 		if (IS_ERR(edge->ipc_regmap)) {
 			ret = PTR_ERR(edge->ipc_regmap);
 			goto put_node;
-- 
